## When NOT to Use

- For bug fixes (use debug skill — refactoring during debugging masks the real issue)
- For adding new features (refactor after the feature works, not during implementation)
- For files outside the agreed scope (scope creep is the enemy of clean refactoring)
- When there are no tests and adding them is out of scope (refactoring without tests is gambling)
